<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author(s). (Year of publication). <em>Title of report</em> 
	(Report No. or additional information about report). Publisher. URL
</blockquote>
<br>
The government department is usually the publisher. If the author and publisher are the same, omit 
the publisher element from the reference. The URL is displayed as a hyperlink.
<br>
<br>
If the report is only available in print, omit the URL element from the reference.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author(s)">Department of Health and Ageing</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2008</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of report">Ageing and aged care in Australia</span></em> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Report No. or additional information about report">Publication No. P3&#45;4147</span>). 
	<span class="hover fake-aref" title="URL">https://webarchive.nla.gov.au/awa/20090918201304/http://health.gov.au/internet/main/publishing.nsf/Content/BFE46F21A3241ECBCA2574BE001A6E06/$File/Ageing_and_Aged_Care.pdf</span>
</blockquote>
